                            <comment id="13023221" author="xuwenhao" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2011 15:04:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a quick and dirty fix. I thought the real fix should also consider the performance as well since the SGD algorithm is really fast.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13023249" author="srowen" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2011 16:30:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Tiny suggestion: I bet you&apos;ll find that &quot;hasOne = actual == 1;&quot; is actually very marginally faster than the if statement (avoids a branch) and is a bit more compact. I also dont know enough to say whether this is the right change. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13023256" author="srowen" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2011 17:02:35 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Er I mean &apos;hasOne &#166;= actual == 1&apos; and that may be too clever. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13037124" author="tdunning" created="Fri, 20 May 2011 23:23:54 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This needs fixing on at least two levels.  First, the documentation should describe why only the binomial case makes sense for ranking and secondly, the code should detect mis-use and complain.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13088481" author="srowen" created="Sun, 21 Aug 2011 22:44:25 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, I committed a variant of this patch to get this moving forward.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13088613" author="hudson" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2011 12:13:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #996 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/996/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/996/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
